OL,3,CPolice officer given marked grave 82
OL,4,Cyears after being killed in WW2 air
OL,5,Craid
OL,7,FHe was remembered along with another
OL,8,FLNER worker, William Milner, who was
OL,9,Falso killed in the raid, during a
OL,10,Fmemorial and dedication service at
OL,11,FYork Cemetery to mark the 82nd
OL,12,Fanniversary.
OL,14,FUntil now, his grave was overgrown and
OL,15,Funmarked. However, his story started
OL,16,Fcoming to light in 2016, through work
OL,17,Fby the British Transport Police (BTP)
OL,18,FHistory Group.
