OL,5,Craid
OL,7,F"His grave at York Cemetery had been
OL,8,Funmarked and unkept for many years.
OL,9,FNow there is a fitting tribute for
OL,10,Feveryone to pay their respects to a
OL,11,Fformer colleague and to honour
OL,12,FRobert's life."
OL,14,FDuring the service, a wreath was also
OL,15,Flaid on the grave of William Milner,
OL,16,Fwho is buried close by.
